{% extends "layout_project.njk" %}
{% block content %}
    {% from "_components.njk" import iframeVideo %}
    <div class = "text-center">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-uppercase">Covid-19 Tracker</h2>
        <p class="item-intro text-muted">Flask API and Android App</p>
    </div>
    <div id="carouselCovidTracker" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
        <!-- Indicators -->
        <ol class="carousel-indicators">
            <li data-target="#carouselCovidTracker" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselCovidTracker" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        </ol>
        <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img src="../img/portfolio/covid-tracker/App_view.png" alt="Chicago"
                        class="d-block w-100 portfolioImgWide">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                    <p>Side view</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="../img/portfolio/covid-tracker/API_response.png" alt="Chicago"
                        class="d-block w-100 portfolioImgWide">
                <div class="carousel-caption">
                    <p>Front view</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        <!-- Left and right controls -->
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselCovidTracker" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselCovidTracker" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
        </a>
    </div>

    <div class="portfolio-description">
        <p>
        I've found mobile browsers are a little slow for image-heavy websites. Back when 
        Covid-19 cases were just starting to start spiking in 2020, I wanted a way to 
        get the latest stats within my community, without directly traveling to the community website.
        </p>

        <p>
        My team and I developed an API in Flask/Python and a rudimentary Android app that does exactly this.
        </p>

        <p>
        The Flask server web-scrapes the community website for a list of cases of COVID, and makes the data available as an API running on Heroku.
        </p>

        <p>
        The Android app contacts the Flask server, and then displays the retrieved data.
        </p>
        <p>Below is a demo video.</p>
        {{ iframeVideo("PEgTP5G2Yj8") }}
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
        <ul class="list-inline">
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/AbhinavA10/CovidTracker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Android App Github Repo</a>           
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/AbhinavA10/Covid-Backend" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Flask Server Github Repo</a>
            </li>
                
            <li>Timeframe: Mar 2020</li>
            <li>Relevant Technologies: Flask, Python, Android</li>
        </ul>
        <a  href="../projects.html">
            <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button">
                <i class="fa fa-times"></i>
                  Close Project
            </button>
        </a>
    </div>
{% endblock %}